    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "This is basically the same as @shoyer's point in https://github.com/pandas-dev/pandas/issues/10000#issuecomment-236238297 right?\r\n\r\nIIRC the current behavior of `dataframe` * `series` is to match the behavior of NumPy to broadcast the last index (columns)?\r\n\r\nI think expecting\r\n\r\n```python\r\ndf[['a', 'b']] * df['c']\r\n```\r\n\r\nto return\r\n\r\n```python\r\nIn [20]: df[['a', 'b']].mul(df['c'], axis=0)\r\nOut[20]:\r\n          a         b\r\n0  1.726545  0.391649\r\n1 -2.189975 -1.825123\r\n2 -0.098067  0.015623\r\n```\r\n\r\nis perfectly reasonable. That said, this would be a big API change, with no clear way of deprecation."
  },
